-(laughs)

30:03.089 --> 30:04.756
I love you.

30:04.839 --> 30:07.172
-I love you.
-Diane: Thank you so much.
It's been an incredible evening.

30:07.255 --> 30:10.339
You raised so much
money for a good cause.
Thank you.

30:10.422 --> 30:13.089
-(piano music playing)
-(indistinct chatter)

30:17.214 --> 30:18.881
Grace:
We're good?

30:19.714 --> 30:21.964
Sylvia:
Joanna...

30:22.047 --> 30:24.798
-Well, you're not gonna
be happy.
-Why?

30:24.881 --> 30:27.047
-I just got paged.
-Mm-hmm?

30:27.130 --> 30:30.506
Shelby McGibbons' lungs
just filled up with fluid.

30:30.589 --> 30:32.422
-Go.
-You want to come?

30:32.506 --> 30:34.047
Legitimate excuse
to duck out early.

30:34.130 --> 30:35.631
The driver could drop me
at the hospital?

30:35.714 --> 30:37.964
Oh, I can't.
I'm on the committee. Go.

30:38.047 --> 30:39.839
-Go, go. Take the driver.
I'll Uber.
-Really? I'm sorry.

30:39.923 --> 30:41.923
I'm sorry.
I'll, I'll call.

30:43.172 --> 30:44.422
(laughs)

30:45.297 --> 30:47.255
-Mm.
-Sally: Where's he going?

30:47.339 --> 30:49.839
Emergency.
One of his patients.

30:49.923 --> 30:53.172
Honestly, staring down cancer
every day with children,

30:53.255 --> 30:55.047
maintaining a sense
of humor all the while.

30:55.130 --> 30:58.255
-How does he do it?
-Grace: I wonder myself.

31:00.047 --> 31:02.881
-(piano music playing)
-(indistinct chatter)

31:14.297 --> 31:16.756
(distant siren blaring)

31:35.714 --> 31:38.089
(slow breathing)

31:42.964 --> 31:44.714
Shelby:
TEN DOLLARS.

31:44.798 --> 31:46.756
Jonathan:
YEP. YOU HAVE MY SOLEMN WORD.

31:46.839 --> 31:48.381
YOU CAN TRUST ME.
I'M A DOCTOR.

31:48.464 --> 31:51.506
Shelby:
TEN BUCKS IF I BEAT LEUKEMIA.

31:51.589 --> 31:52.756
Yeah.

31:52.839 --> 31:54.214
I mean, if you prefer,

31:54.297 --> 31:57.005
I could give you
a whole talk about, um,

31:57.089 --> 31:59.881
you know,
being brave and fighting,

31:59.964 --> 32:02.547
and all that sort of stuff
but I do find,
generally speaking,

32:02.631 --> 32:04.422
money works best.

32:04.506 --> 32:06.756
Shelby:
How 'bout $10,

32:06.839 --> 32:09.464
and when I apply
to medical school,

32:09.547 --> 32:12.255
you write my recommendation.

32:12.339 --> 32:14.172
I don't know.
I don't know, Shelby.

32:14.255 --> 32:15.756
I'd have to see
your transcripts,

32:15.839 --> 32:18.673
because I can't recommend
just anyone.

32:18.756 --> 32:20.339
You could be awful.

32:21.798 --> 32:23.839
Am I going to die?

32:26.381 --> 32:27.964
You're not gonna die.

32:28.964 --> 32:30.297
If you die, I'll kill you.

32:30.381 --> 32:32.130
(Jonathan and Shelby laugh)

32:34.005 --> 32:35.506
(sighs)

32:39.172 --> 32:40.381
(moans softly)

32:40.464 --> 32:42.381
(distant dog barking)

32:47.214 --> 32:49.506
(distant siren blaring)

33:00.923 --> 33:02.089
Hey.

33:07.047 --> 33:09.089
Did everything go okay?

33:12.381 --> 33:14.047
(exhales)

33:18.881 --> 33:20.714
(softly):
Oh, no.

33:21.589 --> 33:23.214
I'm so sorry.

33:26.673 --> 33:29.714
-Honey. (moans)
-Yeah.

33:30.255 --> 33:31.923
(whispers):
Fuck.

33:32.005 --> 33:33.547
(exhales sharply)

33:34.255 --> 33:35.381
Oh.

33:40.464 --> 33:41.714
(groans)

33:52.923 --> 33:54.422
(moans softly)

34:01.756 --> 34:03.923
(both moaning)

34:16.505 --> 34:18.964
(train rattling)

34:23.339 --> 34:25.589
(distant horns honking)

34:35.297 --> 34:37.130
(bird cawing)

34:37.630 --> 34:40.130
(baby cooing)

34:42.589 --> 34:43.964
Miguel:
Where is she?

34:44.047 --> 34:46.214
She's in her studio.

34:46.297 --> 34:48.297
Why hasn't she come back?

34:48.380 --> 34:51.089
(sighs, sniffs)
She's working, okay?

34:52.547 --> 34:54.589
You think you can
take yourself to school today?

34:54.672 --> 34:56.255
Catch the bus outside?

34:56.339 --> 34:57.506
-(baby cries)
-Yeah.

34:57.589 --> 35:00.130
Go get your things.
You're gonna be late.

35:00.214 --> 35:02.631
(baby wailing)

35:05.047 --> 35:07.923
-(crying continues)
-Shh...

35:08.005 --> 35:10.714
-(honking, brakes squealing)
-(indistinct chatter)

35:15.881 --> 35:18.756
(tense music playing)

35:18.839 --> 35:20.881
♪

35:25.506 --> 35:28.005
(horns honking)

35:40.381 --> 35:42.464
-Grace: Henry?
-Uh-huh.

35:42.547 --> 35:44.297
Come on. Have you eaten?

35:44.381 --> 35:47.047
-Yeah.
-We gotta go 'cause I'm, um,

35:47.130 --> 35:49.005
I'm late and I've got
an early session.

35:49.089 --> 35:52.381
-Quick! Put those books away.
-Yeah. Okay.

35:55.297 --> 35:57.172
Mom.

35:57.255 --> 35:59.964
I don't think Dad
is actually allergic
to dogs.

36:00.047 --> 36:01.881
I think he just says it.

36:03.881 --> 36:05.881
Yeah. You're right.

36:05.964 --> 36:08.047
It's not about being allergic.

36:08.130 --> 36:11.589
He would never want me
to tell you this, so don't
say anything, all right?

36:11.673 --> 36:13.297
Okay.

36:13.381 --> 36:16.089
But when he was younger,
he was actually your age,

36:16.172 --> 36:19.506
he was home alone,
he was taking care of
the family dog,

36:19.589 --> 36:21.506
it got out of the house...

36:21.589 --> 36:24.255
and it was hit by a car
and killed.

36:25.839 --> 36:28.714
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

36:28.798 --> 36:31.297
I mean, it was very
traumatic for him.

36:31.381 --> 36:35.047
And it was actually made worse
because his parents...

36:36.589 --> 36:37.839
blamed him for it.

36:37.923 --> 36:41.547
-What?
-Yeah. That's why
he hates talking about it.

36:43.631 --> 36:45.297
What kind of dog?

36:45.381 --> 36:47.964
Um... (scoffs)
What kind of--

36:48.047 --> 36:51.339
I think it was...
It was a small dog.

36:51.422 --> 36:52.589
That's what I know.

36:52.673 --> 36:56.297
Anyway, I honestly don't think
he's ever gotten over it.

36:56.381 --> 36:59.547
Quick. Put everything away,
would you? Let's go.

36:59.631 --> 37:02.339
-Put your coat on.
It's freezing outside.
-All right.

37:06.005 --> 37:09.130
Grace:
AT SOME POINT, YOU ARE
GONNA HAVE TO TALK ABOUT IT.

37:09.214 --> 37:10.673
The why of it all.

37:10.756 --> 37:13.047
It had nothing to do
with us. Or you.

37:13.130 --> 37:14.631
-Bullshit!
-Here we go.

37:14.714 --> 37:16.297
So, what was it about, then?

37:16.381 --> 37:17.297
Just sex?

37:17.381 --> 37:19.130
If I had a clue,
I wouldn't be here

37:19.214 --> 37:20.673
paying these
criminally high rates.

37:20.756 --> 37:22.756
-We are paying these
criminally high rates.
-Would I?

37:22.839 --> 37:24.881
Grace:
That's just a bit deflective,
isn't it, Joseph?

37:24.964 --> 37:28.714
Is it possible that you were
drawn to the secret of it all?

37:28.798 --> 37:31.631
Maybe more than you were
to this other man, Dennis?

37:31.714 --> 37:33.673
The affair got to be
yours alone?

37:33.756 --> 37:37.297
Michael couldn't know about it,
so he couldn't micromanage it?

37:38.839 --> 37:40.297
I don't think that's it.

37:42.881 --> 37:44.506
(phone vibrates)

37:46.214 --> 37:48.798
-(Grace sighs)
-I'm sorry. Are we keeping
you from something?

37:48.881 --> 37:51.631
I apologize.
This is my son's school.

37:51.714 --> 37:55.172
It is programmed for
emergencies only,
so I do have to take it.

38:00.005 --> 38:02.089
(phone thuds)

38:02.172 --> 38:04.589
Now, you said that you knew
Dennis when you were single,

38:04.673 --> 38:06.047
but you never had sex
with him then.

38:06.130 --> 38:07.673
I wasn't even
attracted to him then.

38:07.756 --> 38:09.255
No one was attracted to him.
He's not attractive.

38:09.339 --> 38:11.422
-Okay...
-Grace: Exactly.
Then what changed?

38:11.506 --> 38:14.381
Part of the thrill
of adultery is that

38:14.464 --> 38:17.130
it exists in the shadow

38:17.214 --> 38:18.839
of a primary relationship.

38:18.923 --> 38:20.506
It's the clandestine part of it

38:20.589 --> 38:22.130
that provides
much of the erotic jolt.

38:22.214 --> 38:23.547
Could that have
been it here?

38:24.297 --> 38:25.673
The lie?

38:28.214 --> 38:30.714
What about the fear
of getting caught?

38:32.297 --> 38:34.297
Maybe you wanted to get caught.

38:34.381 --> 38:35.964
Why would I want that?

38:36.047 --> 38:38.756
To show Michael that
he can't control you, after all?

38:40.839 --> 38:43.631
I think this is more about
Michael and your marriage

38:43.714 --> 38:46.756
-than it is about
this other man.
-(door opens)

38:46.839 --> 38:48.255
(door slams)

38:52.839 --> 38:56.422
He doesn't always love when
other people are right.
(chuckles nervously)

39:00.381 --> 39:02.589
So you wanted to get caught.

39:05.673 --> 39:07.506
I think I better check on him.

39:07.589 --> 39:09.839
(footsteps departing)

39:09.923 --> 39:12.047
Man:
So we're gonna try and get
the new protocol

39:12.130 --> 39:15.422
for the pro-bono work,
uh, in place as soon
as possible.

39:16.756 --> 39:19.089
(phone buzzing)

39:20.923 --> 39:22.506
(groans)

39:22.589 --> 39:24.047
(scoffs)

39:24.130 --> 39:27.255
-Sylvia?
-Just a second.

39:27.339 --> 39:30.339
It's my...
It's my daughter's school.
Excuse me.

39:30.422 --> 39:31.923
-Excuse me.
-Man: Sylvia, can it wait?

39:32.005 --> 39:33.047
Two minutes.

39:33.130 --> 39:35.339
-(exhales)
-Woman:
Is this going to affect--

39:35.422 --> 39:37.005
-(door slams)
-Did you hear?

39:37.089 --> 39:38.881
What?

39:38.964 --> 39:41.631
The school? It was a family--
It was a family tragedy?

39:41.714 --> 39:43.589
-A FOURTH GRADER?
-Grace.

39:47.005 --> 39:48.673
It was Elena.

39:49.923 --> 39:52.047
-Grace: WHAT?
-(exhales)

39:52.130 --> 39:53.839
She was found dead.

39:55.381 --> 39:57.506
What?

39:57.589 --> 39:59.547
Sylvia (over phone):
WELL, DIDN'T YOU GET
THE SCHOOL ALERT?

39:59.631 --> 40:01.673
Yes. What happened?

40:01.756 --> 40:02.964
There's been no official word.

40:03.047 --> 40:06.631
At first I heard...
(scoffs) aneurysm, but...

40:06.714 --> 40:09.631
WHAT THE SCHOOL
IS BEING TOLD IS THAT...

40:09.714 --> 40:11.631
SHE WAS MURDERED.

40:13.839 --> 40:15.172
(gasps)

40:16.589 --> 40:18.089
What?

40:18.172 --> 40:20.214
-Sylvia: I KNOW.
-Oh, my God.

40:20.297 --> 40:22.005
And, and apparently,

40:22.089 --> 40:24.297
her son, the poor thing.
discovered her.

40:24.381 --> 40:26.798
God, this is awful. Um...

40:27.798 --> 40:30.422
What do they know?
Do they know who did it?

40:30.506 --> 40:33.923
No. Nobody seems to
really know anything.

40:34.005 --> 40:37.381
-Sylvia: I CANNOT BEAR IT.
THAT POOR WOMAN.
-I know.

40:37.464 --> 40:39.255
And that poor little boy.
It's...

40:39.339 --> 40:42.839
You know,
they're looking for
the husband.

40:42.923 --> 40:45.422
They are. Evidently,
they were having problems.

40:45.506 --> 40:48.089
It's always the fucking husband.

40:48.172 --> 40:50.422
CAN YOU IMAGINE?
LETTING HIS OWN SON

40:50.506 --> 40:52.756
-DISCOVER HIS MOTHER
LIKE THAT?
-(exhales)

40:52.839 --> 40:54.923
(sniffs) You know what?
Actually, I'm right in
the middle of a meeting,

40:55.005 --> 40:57.673
-so I'm gonna call you later
when I know more.
-Grace: YEAH.

41:00.923 --> 41:02.506
(exhales)

41:08.047 --> 41:10.089
Elena:
Did I do something wrong?

41:10.172 --> 41:13.673
-(sighs) No. I just--
-You seem unnerved.

41:13.756 --> 41:17.214
-Really?
-Yeah. Just...
Do I unnerve you?

41:19.589 --> 41:20.631
No.

41:20.714 --> 41:24.255
Well, you would tell me...
if I did something wrong.

41:24.339 --> 41:26.255
You didn't do anything wrong.

41:26.339 --> 41:29.005
-Okay?
-Okay.

41:30.673 --> 41:32.047
(exhales)

41:34.214 --> 41:36.756
♪

41:36.839 --> 41:38.673
Joseph Mendoza:
HOW WELL DID YOU KNOW
ELENA ALVES?

41:38.756 --> 41:41.255
Sally:
Not very well, but, um,
she had just started--

41:41.339 --> 41:43.005
Uh, she was part of
the auction committee.

41:43.089 --> 41:45.005
I arranged to have
her participate.

41:45.089 --> 41:46.255
She was a scholarship mom.

41:46.339 --> 41:48.089
Woman:
I've only met her a few times.

41:48.172 --> 41:49.714
-Just in the schoolyard, here.
-Paul O'Rourke:
Do you remember what time

41:49.798 --> 41:51.673
-you left the fundraiser?
-What time I left?

41:51.756 --> 41:55.005
I think, uh,
I was home by eleven.

41:55.089 --> 41:56.631
And what time did you learn
that something had happened?

41:56.714 --> 41:58.172
Sylvia:
The school sent out an alert.

41:58.255 --> 42:01.172
An alert that went out
from the school on
all of our phones.

42:01.255 --> 42:03.339
-Did you know Elena Alves?
-Sylvia: No. Uh, we've met.

42:03.422 --> 42:04.547
-Mm-hmm.
-I don't know her.

42:04.631 --> 42:06.422
The most time I've
ever spent with her

42:06.506 --> 42:08.506
was at a, a meeting
recently at Sally's.

42:08.589 --> 42:09.964
Do you know if Miguel
took the bus,

42:10.047 --> 42:11.297
or did somebody come
and pick him up?

42:11.381 --> 42:13.381
Well, normally his mom
comes to school
to pick him up.

42:13.464 --> 42:16.005
-Did you know Miguel?
-Uh, yeah, we were
in math together.

42:16.089 --> 42:17.923
Okay. Did you say
you knew Miguel as well?

42:18.005 --> 42:20.005
Yeah, sometimes
we played together
after school.

42:20.089 --> 42:22.923
And did everything
seem okay lately?
He's, he's okay lately?

42:24.798 --> 42:27.339
(line ringing)

42:27.422 --> 42:29.589
(siren blaring)

42:30.839 --> 42:32.881
(phone ringing)

42:32.964 --> 42:34.381
Jonathan (on voicemail):
HELLO, THIS IS JONATHAN FRASER.

42:34.464 --> 42:35.673
I CAN'T ANSWER YOUR CALL
RIGHT NOW,

42:35.756 --> 42:38.047
BUT I WILL GET BACK TO YOU
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

42:38.130 --> 42:41.381
IF THIS IS A MEDICAL EMERGENCY,
PLEASE CALL 911,

42:41.464 --> 42:44.130
OR GO TO THE EMERGENCY ROOM.

42:44.214 --> 42:46.381
Hi, sweetheart.
It's, it's me.

42:46.464 --> 42:49.089
Um, can you give me a call,

42:49.172 --> 42:50.589
'cause something
came up at school.

42:50.673 --> 42:54.172
E-everything's fine.
Henry is fine, but I...

42:54.255 --> 42:57.422
I just, I just want to
fill you in. Um...

42:59.172 --> 43:00.756
I hope Cleveland is good.

43:00.839 --> 43:03.381
-I love you, Uh--
-O'Rourke: Mrs. Fraser.

43:03.464 --> 43:05.881
I'm Detective Paul O'Rourke.
23rd precinct.

43:05.964 --> 43:08.297
Oh, my God.
What happened?
Is it my son?

43:08.381 --> 43:10.881
No, it's not about your son.
I'm sorry if we frightened you.
We--

43:10.964 --> 43:12.631
We do that sometimes.

43:12.714 --> 43:14.506
Grace:
Right. Um...

43:14.589 --> 43:16.464
I'm Detective Joseph Mendoza.
NYPD.

43:16.547 --> 43:17.798
We just want to talk
for a minute.

43:17.881 --> 43:19.714
Can you please just
tell me what happened?

43:19.798 --> 43:21.005
Well, the mother of a child

43:21.089 --> 43:22.923
who attends your son's school
was killed.

43:23.005 --> 43:24.381
-I'm sure you heard of that.

43:24.464 --> 43:25.881
-Yeah.
-The school sent out a message.

43:25.964 --> 43:26.923
I'm so sorry. I just--

43:27.005 --> 43:28.214
No, no. No need to apologize.

43:28.297 --> 43:29.589
-I got two kids.
-Grace: Right.

43:29.673 --> 43:31.714
We just want to ask
a few questions,
if that's okay.

43:33.130 --> 43:34.464
Of course.

43:38.172 --> 43:41.005
I didn't know it was
Mrs. Alves till, um...

43:41.089 --> 43:42.673
until I spoke to a friend.

43:42.756 --> 43:45.089
-And who was the friend?
-Um...

43:45.172 --> 43:46.756
Sylvia Steinetz.

43:46.839 --> 43:49.923
She and I are part of
a committee at the school
that we serve on.

43:50.005 --> 43:52.047
-The, uh, auction committee?
-Mm-hmm.

43:52.130 --> 43:53.798
She just joined.

43:53.881 --> 43:56.089
Mendoza:
And what time did you
learn of her death?

43:56.172 --> 43:58.422
Hmm.
Let me check my phone.

44:01.464 --> 44:04.547
Uh, at 2:46 p.m.

44:04.631 --> 44:07.255
-From, uh, Sylvia Steinetz?
-Grace: Yes.

44:07.339 --> 44:10.339
Is that important?
What time I got the call?

44:10.422 --> 44:12.130
Mendoza:
Well, you're a shrink, right?

44:12.214 --> 44:15.005
You only ask the
important stuff?

44:16.381 --> 44:19.506
She wasn't, um,
a patient of mine,
Mrs. Alves.

44:19.589 --> 44:23.130
She was a--
She-- I mean,
I wasn't treating her.

44:23.214 --> 44:24.714
How well did you know her?

44:24.798 --> 44:29.255
Uh, not well.
As I said, she'd only
just joined the committee.

44:29.339 --> 44:30.798
And you saw her last when?

44:30.881 --> 44:33.798
Grace:
I saw her last night
at the benefit.

44:33.881 --> 44:36.339
Mendoza:
And you didn't talk to her
after that?

44:36.422 --> 44:38.673
-No.
-Mendoza:
Did you notice anyone

44:38.756 --> 44:42.089
Mrs. Alves might have spoken to?

44:44.589 --> 44:48.214
I mean, there were just
some men who were
paying her

44:48.297 --> 44:50.130
special attention.

44:50.214 --> 44:52.214
-What do you mean,
special attention?
-No, I mean,

44:52.297 --> 44:55.422
the, the special attention
that men sometimes

44:55.506 --> 44:57.381
-pay to a woman.
-Mendoza: Mm.

44:58.255 --> 45:00.839
And what about
Mrs. Alves' husband?

45:00.923 --> 45:02.381
Was he there last night?

45:03.214 --> 45:05.339
Not to my knowledge.

45:05.422 --> 45:07.881
I mean, I never met him, so...

45:12.172 --> 45:14.381
Do you suspect
the husband of this?

45:14.464 --> 45:17.381
Right now, we're just,
uh, gathering facts.

45:17.464 --> 45:21.422
Would it be possible for us
to speak to your husband?

45:21.506 --> 45:25.130
Um, well, um, why?

45:25.214 --> 45:27.255
Well, he might have
seen something.

45:27.339 --> 45:30.381
Oh. No. No, he didn't.

45:30.464 --> 45:33.464
So you've spoken to him
since this news came to light?

45:33.547 --> 45:35.589
No, but anything that
he would have seen,

45:35.673 --> 45:37.506
-I would have seen, so...
-Where's your husband now?

45:37.589 --> 45:38.923
He's in Cleveland.

45:39.005 --> 45:41.172
He's at an oncology
convention.

45:41.255 --> 45:42.506
Mendoza:
Where's he staying?

45:42.589 --> 45:43.547
Grace:
I think at a Hyatt,

45:43.631 --> 45:45.172
-or something.
-When did he go there?

45:45.255 --> 45:46.881
Uh, this morning.

45:46.964 --> 45:48.714
-Early.
-(door opens, then closes)

45:48.798 --> 45:51.172
-Henry: Mom.
-Grace: Oh, Henry.

45:51.255 --> 45:54.172
-(sighs)
-Henry: Um, orchestra
ran over.

45:54.255 --> 45:56.172
-Grace: Mm-hmm.
-Wh-what's going on?

45:56.255 --> 45:57.714
Grace:
Um, I'm just talking
to these men.

45:57.798 --> 45:59.255
Could you go to your room,
and I'll, um,

45:59.339 --> 46:00.756
I'll be up in a minute?

46:00.839 --> 46:03.339
-I'll make you a snack.
-Is everything okay?

46:03.422 --> 46:05.297
Grace:
Yes. Yep. Everything's fine.

46:05.381 --> 46:07.756
I just need you
to go upstairs,

46:07.839 --> 46:10.339
and, um, I'll be right there.

46:11.339 --> 46:13.255
Off you go.
I'll be right there.

46:13.339 --> 46:15.005
-Okay.
-Grace: Good.

46:17.673 --> 46:19.214
Go on. (laughs)

46:21.339 --> 46:23.381
Did your son know
the Alves boy?

46:23.464 --> 46:25.923
Um, no. No.

46:26.005 --> 46:29.130
I mean, they're...
They're in different grades.

46:29.214 --> 46:31.422
Yeah, but it's kind of
a small school, isn't it?

46:31.506 --> 46:34.422
That's what I read
on the website.
Small school,

46:34.506 --> 46:36.756
individual attention.

46:36.839 --> 46:39.172
That's why it costs
the big bucks, right?

46:42.714 --> 46:45.089
What is the tuition there?

46:45.172 --> 46:46.839
How much do you pay?

46:46.923 --> 46:50.464
Um, it's...

46:50.547 --> 46:52.673
-$50,000 a year.
-Oof.

46:52.756 --> 46:56.130
Fifty grand. How do you think
they could afford that?
The Alveses?

46:56.214 --> 46:59.589
I mean, I think
it was a scholarship.

46:59.673 --> 47:03.631
But, I don't really have
any knowledge of, uh,

47:03.714 --> 47:06.839
the Alves' financial
circumstances.

47:08.798 --> 47:10.714
Are we upsetting you,
doctor?

47:12.923 --> 47:17.214
(sighs) If there's anything,
anything else I can do.

47:17.714 --> 47:19.005
Sure.

47:21.005 --> 47:22.214
Here's my card.

47:22.297 --> 47:23.756
My cell phone.

47:24.589 --> 47:26.214
If you can think of
anything else.

47:26.297 --> 47:29.255
I will, I will give you a call.

47:29.589 --> 47:30.881
Good.

47:30.964 --> 47:32.172
Mendoza:
Thank you.

47:32.255 --> 47:35.047
-(door opens)
-O'Rourke: Right. Thanks.

47:35.130 --> 47:37.339
-(door closes)
-Henry: What was that about?

47:37.422 --> 47:38.631
-What?
-The police.

47:38.714 --> 47:41.255
-Henry...
-Are they here
for the murder?

47:43.255 --> 47:46.255
-Yeah.
-Oh, I saw it on my phone.

47:46.339 --> 47:48.422
-Really?
-Yeah.

47:51.964 --> 47:53.798
They mentioned Reardon.

47:54.923 --> 47:58.381
Oh. Did you, um...
Did you know the boy?

47:58.464 --> 48:00.214
I think his name is Miguel?

48:01.964 --> 48:03.964
I don't think so.

48:06.381 --> 48:08.714
-Thank you.
-Kind of scary, huh?

48:08.798 --> 48:10.464
This happening at your school?

48:10.547 --> 48:12.631
How you feeling about it?

48:13.339 --> 48:15.172
Did the father do it?

48:17.422 --> 48:18.923
It's...

48:19.964 --> 48:21.589
It's too soon to know.

48:21.673 --> 48:22.798
Did you know her?

48:24.422 --> 48:26.756
Um, hmm?

48:26.839 --> 48:29.047
The mom who got...

48:29.130 --> 48:30.589
Did you know her?

48:31.881 --> 48:33.547
Not really. I mean, she was--

48:33.631 --> 48:35.422
She was on
the auction committee.

48:37.172 --> 48:38.381
Was she nice?

48:38.464 --> 48:40.381
(exhales) Yeah.

48:40.464 --> 48:43.506
Yeah, she was very nice.
She...

48:43.589 --> 48:46.381
She seemed a little sad.

48:50.005 --> 48:52.714
O'Rourke:
WHERE DO YOU GO TO SCHOOL?
YOU GO TO REARDON?

48:53.673 --> 48:56.047
What-- Okay.
What grade are you in?

48:57.422 --> 48:59.381
-Fourth.
-Okay.

49:00.297 --> 49:01.839
Do you like it?

49:02.506 --> 49:03.673
It's all right.

49:03.756 --> 49:05.589
So, you were gonna
go to school,

49:05.673 --> 49:08.589
but instead, did--
You went where?

49:08.673 --> 49:11.798
-My mom's studio.
-She's a, an artist?

49:13.339 --> 49:16.881
I know it's hard.
We gotta find out who did this.

49:17.923 --> 49:20.714
(camera shutter clicking)

49:22.089 --> 49:25.381
♪

49:36.255 --> 49:38.714
-Hey.
-Hi.

49:41.005 --> 49:43.339
(clicking on phone screen)

49:47.297 --> 49:48.422
Hey, honey. Um,

49:48.506 --> 49:50.172
I'm sure you're at some
scintillating dinner,

49:50.255 --> 49:51.589
but I really
need you to call me

49:51.673 --> 49:53.255
and talk about
this school incident.

49:53.339 --> 49:56.547
It's nothing bad with Henry,
but can you call me, please?

49:58.047 --> 50:00.255
(clock ticking)

50:03.005 --> 50:04.798
(tapping on phone screen)

50:04.881 --> 50:06.297
(exhales)

50:06.381 --> 50:07.839
(phone bloops)

50:07.923 --> 50:10.422
-(sighs)
-(distant phone vibrating)

50:24.255 --> 50:26.422
(tapping on phone screen)

50:26.506 --> 50:29.547
-(phone bloops)
-(distant phone vibrates)

50:35.881 --> 50:37.756
(clattering)

50:43.422 --> 50:45.547
(breathing shakily)

50:47.130 --> 50:48.422
(drawer slams)

50:50.714 --> 50:52.839
(breathes heavily)

51:09.422 --> 51:11.589
(tapping on phone screen)

51:16.964 --> 51:19.547
(line ringing)

51:19.631 --> 51:21.506
Man 1 (over phone):
HYATT REGENCY AT THE ARCADE.

51:21.589 --> 51:24.047
Um, Jonathan Fraser, please.

51:24.130 --> 51:26.798
-Man 1: IS HE A GUEST?
-Yes.

51:26.881 --> 51:29.172
Man 1:
I'M SORRY. I'M NOT SEEING
A JONATHAN FRASER.

51:29.255 --> 51:32.506
WOULD IT BE UNDER
ANOTHER NAME?

51:32.589 --> 51:35.005
Woman 1 (over phone):
HYATT PLACE INDEPENDENCE.
THIS IS JESSICA.

51:35.089 --> 51:37.923
Uh, Jonathan Fraser's
room, please.

51:38.005 --> 51:40.881
-Jessica: I'M SORRY.
I DON'T SEE ANY RESERVATION.
-(exhales sharply)

51:40.964 --> 51:42.547
Woman 2 (over phone):
HYATT CLEVELAND LEGACY.

51:42.631 --> 51:44.714
Could you put me through
to Jonathan Fraser's room,
please?

51:44.798 --> 51:49.964
-Woman 2:
UH, CAN YOU SPELL THAT?
-Fraser. F-R-A-S-E-R.

51:51.839 --> 51:54.589
-Woman 2: UH, YES.
TRANSFERRING YOU NOW.
-(sighs)

51:54.673 --> 51:56.881
(line ringing)

51:59.714 --> 52:01.547
Woman 3 (over phone):
HELLO?

52:03.005 --> 52:05.130
-Uh...
-Woman 3: WHO IS THIS?

52:06.589 --> 52:08.214
Who are you?

52:08.297 --> 52:10.172
Woman 3: EXCUSE ME?

52:11.422 --> 52:13.005
Uh...

52:13.089 --> 52:16.422
Can you, um, put me through
to, uh, Jonathan Fraser, please?

52:16.506 --> 52:19.381
-(clears throat)
-Woman 3: UH, HOLD ON.

52:20.464 --> 52:22.047
JONATHAN?

52:25.714 --> 52:27.381
Man 2 (over phone):
THIS IS JONATHAN.

52:28.172 --> 52:31.005
Uh, J-Jonathan Fraser?

52:31.089 --> 52:33.214
Man 2 (over phone):
YES. WHO IS THIS?

52:33.297 --> 52:36.089
I'm, I'm sorry. Um...

52:36.172 --> 52:38.005
Sorry.

52:56.714 --> 52:59.714
(intense orchestral
music playing)

53:06.673 --> 53:10.089
♪

54:10.673 --> 54:11.631
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

54:11.923 --> 54:13.756
GRACE FRASER: <i>I don't know</i>
<i>where your father is.</i>

54:14.798 --> 54:17.506
He's not returning calls,
he's not returning my emails.

54:18.381 --> 54:20.089
HENRY FRASER:
<i>Mom, you're acting strange.</i>

54:20.381 --> 54:21.631
<i>Don't worry, it's fine.</i>

54:22.547 --> 54:25.130
If you know something,
this would be the right time

54:25.214 --> 54:26.339
to tell us what it is.

54:29.172 --> 54:31.756
GRACE: <i>Nothing about this</i>
<i>makes any sense.</i>

54:32.172 --> 54:34.172
I just need to get the truth.

54:34.714 --> 54:36.005
Did you guys hear?

54:36.589 --> 54:38.089
<i>The husband just turned</i>
<i>himself in.</i>

54:38.631 --> 54:39.798
Of course it was the husband.

54:40.589 --> 54:41.631
<i>It's always the husband.</i>

54:42.964 --> 54:46.130
DETECTIVE: <i>Exactly how well</i>
<i>did you know Elena Alves?</i>

54:47.005 --> 54:48.631
HALEY FITZGERALD: <i>They still</i>
<i>think you're withholding.</i>

54:48.714 --> 54:49.673
Why?

54:50.673 --> 54:53.005
Because it's what
rich people do.

54:54.881 --> 54:56.714
<i>They conceal the ugly truths.</i>

54:57.673 --> 54:59.297
-(SCREAMS)
-(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

54:59.839 --> 55:01.714
FRANKLIN REINHART: <i>You think</i>
<i>you can handle everything.</i>

55:04.130 --> 55:05.381
This is bigger than you.

55:07.214 --> 55:09.339
Exactly how weak
do you think I am?

55:10.089 --> 55:11.381
(WHISPERING)
<i>I will fix this.</i>

55:12.089 --> 55:13.172
<i>I'll fix this.</i>

55:14.214 --> 55:16.172
I've got a feeling your daughter
is hiding something.

55:16.506 --> 55:18.130
<i>For all I know, she's</i>
<i>an accomplice.</i>

55:18.339 --> 55:21.381
GRACE: (WHISPERING)
<i>I will fix this.</i>

55:21.923 --> 55:23.214
(SCREAMS)

55:25.047 --> 55:26.214
GRACE: <i>I'll fix this.</i>

55:27.005 --> 55:28.214
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
